

Nectar Lifesciences Limited is an integrated pharmaceutical company in India that manufactures generic products.

The company was promoted by Sanjiv Goyal and incorporated in June 1995 as Surya Medicare Limited, with financial collaboration from the Punjab State Industrial Development Corp. (PSIDC). Its name was changed to Nectar Lifesciences in Mar. 2004 after it bought out PSIDC. Nectar Lifesciences went public in July 2005 with simultaneous listings on Bombay Stock Exchange and the National Stock Exchange of India.

The current market capitalization is about INR 5.5 billion (US$ 120 million).

Nectar Lifesciences manufactures oral and sterile active pharmaceutical ingredients, finished dosages and phytochemicals. The company is also in business of providing leading pharmaceutical organizations with contract research and manufacturing services. It also Manufactures Empty Hard Gelatin Capsules.





